      <span class="eyebrow">Longevity · The Problem</span>
      <h2>Aging starts in your cells.</h2>
      <p class="thesis-lede">Inside every cell is a molecule called <strong>NAD⁺</strong> — the spark your body uses to turn food into energy, repair DNA, and keep cells working the way they did in your twenties. But NAD⁺ doesn't hold. It falls year after year, and by midlife research suggests it can drop to roughly <strong>half</strong> of youthful levels.*</p>
    </div>
    <div class="prob-grid reveal" id="probGrid">
      <div class="prob-card">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M13 2 4 14h6l-1 8 9-12h-6z"/></svg>
        <h3>Energy runs low</h3>
        <p>Less NAD⁺ means the mitochondria — your cells' power plants — make less usable energy. It surfaces as afternoon crashes and slower recovery.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="prob-card">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M20 12a8 8 0 1 1-2.4-5.7"/><path d="M20 4v4h-4"/></svg>
